column5: awesome,  congrats
Well done!!   I just finished 4 weeks of a 6 week course...struggled every day to stay awake.  Get all that classroom room stuff done while you are young.

Nice Job. Now here is a EASY question for you. It's time to FISH or cut bait, you make the choice.  My oldest son has been studing for 3 week now to take his medical board exams in 2 weeks. If he passes I just might have to call him "Doc"
A doctor of fishing Matt ?      They don't stand a chance.
Awesome Matty...so soon we'll be calling you Doc  .  Good stuff, and sounds like an interesting thesis topic.  Maureen

My funding last for another two years,  so hopefully thats how long it will take me. It has taken me 2 years to get all my course work done, and now i need to get some research and writing done. I am so sick of school, but im gonna stick with it until i finish. During the summer i will be taking it easy and spending about 5 weeks in Ontario musky fishin.

I just got news I passed my comprehensive exam. 3 full days of torture 8 hours per day of sitting in front of a computer, and in total 60 pages of writing about urban planning.  I advanced to doctoral candidacy and now all thats left is to write a little thesis. Those fish better watch it now.
Congrats  Is there such a thing as a "little thesis" ??
Way to go..Congratulations!!  Go get those fish!  bly
Congratulations, it must have been easy for you to compete with all those hillbillies in the classroom.
Way to go  Congrats  Joey
Congrats!!  The hard work obviously paid off.
Congrat's matty, what's the thesis on?  John..
Atta boy!
Very good news indeed, congrats...
Good onya Matt! Well done and have a great summer.
A hearty Attaboy!.
Congrats!  Sounds like you are on your way to creating wealth and luck!  Now go fishing to reward yourself  Tony
Fantastic, well done!
congratulations! now you can have a stress-free and fish-ful summer
Congrats Matty! Start typing...and typing...and typing....

thanks for the kind words all. I do research with natural disasters and i want to focus on emergency rescue services and take a social justice equity perspective, ie do the poor get equal access to emergency services as the rich. This is where the fun begins.

WOW!! Congrats!! Urban Planning...so you head to an undeveloped area....look around...find out if any fish are there and if so then recommend leave it as is??? haha.  Seriously...it's a great accomplishment...enjoy your summer before the "little" thesis comes up!!
Great news. Now they can hire you as the new head of FEMA & we can actually have someone in charge that knows what the hell they're doing.

Matt, congratulations on moving a step closer to the finish line!  As someone who was in your shoes not too long ago, I remember how stressful it was to go through the comp exam process--reading tons, studying tons, writing tons, and then fending off all these exam committee members picking on every minute detail of my answers.  You've come a long way, but brace yourself as that "little" thesis can bring a lot of nasty suprises down the road.  Mine was supposed to take a couple of years; I ended up spending nearly four years, and the little thesis turned into a 400-page tome, so dry and boring that even my wife couldn't get beyond the first few pages!  But all that misery is to come later on; for now, enjoy your accomplishment as much as you can.  Congrats once again!  Oh yeah, as someone else already said, start typing!
Way to go Matty! Congrats!
LOL those KY's are called "BRIARS"  TG  Well done Matt    now hit the fish you deserve it!  Whopper
Congrats!  Where do you go to scool, U of L?
yup,the university of louisville.

Man, you guys are going to get stomped in Morgantown this fall... Let's go Mountaineers!

Sorry, couldn't resist.
CONGRATS----Now go get out smarted by a fish with a brain the size of rice.
